This paper investigates the coexistence of Wi-Fi and LTE-Unlicensed technologies, which falls under the category of networked and internet technologies (cs.NI). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and probability theory to analyze the performance of Wi-Fi in the presence of LTE-U, which suggests the involvement of information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) subcategories. The paper also deals with fairness and air time sharing, which can be related to system and control (cs.SY) subcategory. Lastly, the paper discusses interference and models the LTE-U interference, which can be related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) subcategory.
